-4.354 16.765-10.885l-8.171-2.842c-1.15 4.233-4.297 6.591-8.775 6.591Z"></path></svg></a></div></div><div><main><article id="content"><div><ul><li><a href="https://www.theverge.com/news">News</a><span>/</span></li><li><a href="https://www.theverge.com/tech">Tech</a><span>/</span></li><li><a href="https://www.theverge.com/nintendo">Nintendo</a></li></ul><h2>Nintendo’s next Lego console will be a Game Boy</h2><div><div><div><h2>Nintendo’s next Lego console will be a Game Boy</h2><p><span><span> / </span><h2>Lego and Nintendo are preparing a Game Boy block kit for release this fall.</h2></span></p></div><div><p><span>By</span> <span><span></span> <span><a href="https://www.theverge.com/authors/andrew-webster">Andrew Webster</a></span><span>, <span>an entertainment editor covering streaming, virtual worlds, and every single Pokémon video game. Andrew joined The Verge in 2012, writing over 4,000 stories.</span></span></span></p><p><time datetime="2025-01-09T17:22:40.162Z"> <!-- -->Jan 9, 2025, 5:22 PM UTC</time></p><div><h2>Share this story</h2></div></div></div><div><figure><span><span></span></span><p><cite>Image: Nintendo / Lego</cite></p></figure></div></div></div><div><div id="zephr-anchor"><p>While we’re all waiting for <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/8/24339396/nintendo-switch-2-genki-ces-2025">official news about the Switch 2</a>, Nintendo has gone ahead and announced a very different kind of console. The company is teasing a collaboration with Lego that will see the original grey brick known as a Game Boy rendered in Lego blocks. There are no details yet, aside from the fact that it’ll be out in October, but it’s likely an official reveal is coming soon.</p><div><p>This isn’t the first collab between the two companies, as there have been <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/25/24205955/lego-nintendo-super-mario-yoshi-snes-gaming-sdcc">a handful of Lego sets based on Nintendo properties</a>, along with <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2020/7/14/21322481/lego-nintendo-nes-super-mario-interactive-set-replica">a blocky rendition of the NES</a>.</p></div><div><h3>Related</h3><ul><li><a href="https://www.theverge.com/21578775/lego-nintendo-game-boy-fan-model-nick-lever-masters">The perfect Lego Nintendo Game Boy doesn’t exist...</a></li></ul></div><div><p>If you’re keeping track, this is part of a lengthy string of non-Switch 2 announcements and launches that Nintendo has made over the last few months. <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24256070/nintendo-museum-kyoto-tour-shigeru-miyamoto">A Nintendo museum opened in Kyoto in October</a>, and after that the company released <a href="https://www.theverge.com/24273422/nintendo-alarmo-review-alarm-clock">an alarm clock called Alarmo</a>, <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/30/24284073/nintendo-music-streaming-app-switch-online-subscribers">started a music streaming service full of classic gaming tunes</a>, and <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/21/24275596/nintendo-switch-online-beta-playtest-program-leak-mmo">kicked off a test for a mysterious MMO</a>. At this rate, <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/22/24276650/nintendo-switch-2-predictions-playtest-alarmo">it’s almost pointless to guess what Nintendo will do next</a>.</p></div></div><div><div><p>Most Popular</p><p>Most Popular</p><ol><li><a href="https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/8/24338974/samsung-galaxy-subscription-smartphones-ballie"><h2>Samsung is rolling out a smartphone subscription next month</h2></a><hr></li><li><a href="https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/8/24338969/google-home-hubs-local-control-matter"><h2>Google Home hubs can now work locally thanks to Matter</h2></a><hr></li><li><a href="https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/8/24338999/nvidia-rtx-5070-vs-rtx4090-performance-price"><h2>Can Nvidia’s RTX 5070 really deliver RTX 4090 performance for $549?</h2></a><hr></li><li><a href="https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/8/24339396/nintendo-switch-2-genki-ces-2025"><h2>Is this the Nintendo Switch 2?</h2></a><hr></li><li><a href="https://www.theverge.com/2025/1/4/24307731/ces-2025-tvs-gaming-smart-home-wearables-news"><h2>CES 2025: all the news, gadgets, and surprises</h2></a><hr></li></ol></div><div data-native-ad-id="container"><div><p><span>From our sponsor</span></p><h3><a data-native-ad-id="title" href="http://theverge.com/"></a></h3><a href="http://theverge.com/"><p><span data-native-ad-id="preamble">Advertiser Content From</span></p></a></div></div></div></div></article></main><div><h2>More from this stream<!-- --> <a href="https://www.theverge.com/23793880/lego-adults-welcome-new-sets-storystream">Lego isn’t just for kids: the latest news for nostalgic adults and adult budgets</a></h2><ul><li><h3><a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/7/24290481/legos-3011-piece-the-endurance-sets-sail-on-november-29th">Lego’s 3,011-piece The Endurance sets sail on November 29th.</a></h3><p><time datetime="2024-11-07T16:48:59.726Z"> <!-- -->Nov 7, 2024, 4:48 PM UTC</time></p></li><li><h3><a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/17/24272696/legos-new-x-men-the-x-mansion-set-includes-the-first-gambit-minifigure">Lego’s new X-Men: The X-Mansion set includes the first Gambit minifigure.</a></h3><p><time datetime="2024-10-17T15:52:29.663Z"> <!-- -->Oct 17, 2024, 3:52 PM UTC</time></p></li><li><h3><a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/17/24246637/jabba-the-hutt-has-his-own-500-lego-set">Jabba the Hutt has his own $500 Lego set.</a></h3><p><time datetime="2024-09-17T16:51:07.389Z"> <!-- -->Sep 17, 2024, 4:51 PM UTC</time></p></li><li><h3><a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/17/24180563/lego-star-wars-sets-will-never-be-the-same">Lego Star Wars sets will never be the same.</a></h3><p><time datetime="2024-06-17T22:46:49.437Z"> <!-- -->Jun 17, 2024, 10:46 PM UTC</time></p></li></ul><a href="https://www.theverge.com/23793880/lego-adults-welcome-new-sets-storystream">See all <!-- -->138<!-- --> stories</a> </div></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
